  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I tell if a guy likes me or is just using me?",
  "response": "Determining whether a guy genuinely likes you or is just using you can be tricky, but paying attention to his actions, intentions, and consistency can help you gain clarity. Here are some signs to consider:\n\n### Signs He Genuinely Likes You:\n1. **He Prioritizes You**: He makes time for you, even when he\u2019s busy, and includes you in his plans.\n2. **He Shows Interest in Your Life**: He asks about your day, your interests, and your feelings, and remembers the details.\n3. **He Respects Your Boundaries**: He doesn\u2019t pressure you into things you\u2019re uncomfortable with and respects your decisions.\n4. **He Invests in the Relationship**: He puts effort into getting to know you, building trust, and creating meaningful moments together.\n5. **He\u2019s Consistent**: His actions and words align over time, and he doesn\u2019t disappear or act hot-and-cold.\n6. **He Introduces You to His World**: He wants you to meet his friends and family and includes you in important parts of his life.\n7. **He Supports You**: He encourages your goals, dreams, and well-being, even when it doesn\u2019t directly benefit him.\n\n### Signs He May Be Using You:\n1. **He\u2019s Only Around When It\u2019s Convenient**: He only contacts you when he wants something (e.g., attention, validation, or physical intimacy) and disappears afterward.\n2. **He Avoids Commitment or Labels**: He avoids serious conversations about the relationship or keeps things vague.\n3. **He Doesn\u2019t Invest in You**: He doesn\u2019t make an effort to understand or support your needs, feelings, or goals.\n4. **He\u2019s Self-Centered**: The relationship revolves around his needs, and he doesn\u2019t consider yours.\n5. **He\u2019s Inconsistent or Unreliable**: His behavior is unpredictable, and he doesn\u2019t follow through on promises.\n6. **He Keeps You Secret**: He avoids introducing you to his friends or family and keeps the relationship hidden.\n7. **He Manipulates or Guilt-Trips You**: He uses emotional manipulation to get what he wants or makes you feel bad for setting boundaries.\n\n### How to Assess the Situation:\n1. **Observe His Actions**: Words can be misleading, but consistent actions often reveal true intentions.\n2. **Communicate Your Needs**: Share your feelings and expectations openly to see how he responds.\n3. **Trust Your Gut**: If something feels off, it\u2019s worth exploring why you feel that way.\n4. **Set Boundaries**: Establish clear boundaries and see if he respects them.\n5. **Give It Time**: Genuine feelings and intentions often become clearer over time.\n\nIf you\u2019re still unsure, consider discussing your concerns with someone you trust or reflecting on whether the relationship makes you feel valued and respected. You deserve someone who truly cares about you and treats you with kindness and respect.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
